<div id="cbanner" style="height:96px">
<h2><img src="/gfx/bnrs/research_744x96z.jpg"
   style="width:744px;height:96px;border:0"  alt="Research News &amp; Features" /></h2>
</div>
<div id="cpad">

<p>
Following are news releases, features and updates about GISS research written by
NASA news services, GISS personnel, and affiliated offices.
</p><div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/people-of-nasa/goddard-people/jennifer-krottinger-designing-ways-to-serve/">Jennifer Krottinger: Designing Ways to Serve</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/people-of-nasa/goddard-people/jennifer-krottinger-designing-ways-to-serve/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2024/202403_news_krottinger_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Photo of Jennifer Krottinger" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>At NASA’s Goddard Institute for Space Studies in New York City, Jennifer Krottinger pairs her artistic vision with a passion for public service.<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2024-03-05)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/people-of-nasa/goddard-people/jennifer-krottinger-designing-ways-to-serve/">Go to NASA Release</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/can-volcanic-super-eruptions-lead-to-major-cooling-study-suggests-no/">Can Volcanic Super Eruptions Lead to Major Cooling? Study Suggests No</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/can-volcanic-super-eruptions-lead-to-major-cooling-study-suggests-no/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2024/202403_news_volcanos_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Satellite photo of Mount Etna erupting in 2002" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>New research suggests that sunlight-blocking particles from an extreme eruption would not cool surface temperatures on Earth as severely as previously estimated.<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2024-03-01)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/can-volcanic-super-eruptions-lead-to-major-cooling-study-suggests-no/">Go to NASA Release</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-launches-new-climate-mission-to-study-ocean-atmosphere/">NASA Launches New Climate Mission to Study Ocean, Atmosphere</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-launches-new-climate-mission-to-study-ocean-atmosphere/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2024/202402_news_pacelaunch_1462x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Photo of the rocket carrying PACE lifting off the launch pad" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>NASA’s PACE satellite mission to study ocean health, air quality, and the effects of a changing climate for the benefit of humanity launched successfully into orbit at 1:33 a.m. EST, Thursday, February 8. <br />
<span class="feature_date">(2024-02-08)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-launches-new-climate-mission-to-study-ocean-atmosphere/">Go to NASA Release</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-analysis-confirms-2023-as-warmest-year-on-record/">NASA Analysis Confirms 2023 as Warmest Year on Record</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-analysis-confirms-2023-as-warmest-year-on-record/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2024/202401_news_gistemp_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Line plot of global temperature anomalies showing the curve for months of 2023 overlying curves of previous years" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>
Earth's average surface temperature in 2023 was the warmest on record, according to an analysis by NASA. Global temperatures last year were around 1.2&#176;C above the 1851-1980 baseline.
<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2024-01-12)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-analysis-confirms-2023-as-warmest-year-on-record/">Go to NASA Release</a><br \>+ <a href="https://data.giss.nasa.gov/gistemp/">Go to Dataset</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/152313/five-factors-to-explain-the-record-heat-in-2023">Five Factors to Explain the Record Heat in 2023</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/152313/five-factors-to-explain-the-record-heat-in-2023"><img src="/gfx/spot/2024/202401_feature_gistempeo_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Screen capture from an animation showing the rise of CO2 in Earth;s atmosphere over the past century and how the gas circulates around the globe" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>NASA announced that 2023 was the hottest year on record. What caused the year to be so hot? Here is a breakdown of the primary factors that scientists considered.<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2024-01-13)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/152313/five-factors-to-explain-the-record-heat-in-2023">Go to NASA EO Feature</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/new-nasa-satellite-to-unravel-mysteries-about-clouds-aerosols/">New NASA Satellite To Unravel Mysteries About Clouds, Aerosols</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/new-nasa-satellite-to-unravel-mysteries-about-clouds-aerosols/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202312_news_pace12_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Colorful satellite image of clouds over the ocean." /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>NASA’s upcoming PACE mission will offer important insights on airborne particles of sea salt, smoke, human-made pollutants, and dust by observing how they interact with light.<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-12-12)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/new-nasa-satellite-to-unravel-mysteries-about-clouds-aerosols/">Go to NASA Release</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nccs.nasa.gov/news-events/nccs-highlights/nasa-deepened-our-understanding-of-earth-in-2023">How NASA Deepened Our Understanding of Earth in 2023</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nccs.nasa.gov/news-events/nccs-highlights/nasa-deepened-our-understanding-of-earth-in-2023"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202312_feature_earth2023_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Sample frame from an animation of ocean currents" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>
In 2023, the NASA Center for Climate Simulation and NASA Science Managed Cloud Environment provided computing resources to enable research and accelerate scientific discoveries that deepen our understanding of Earth and better prepare for its changing climates.
<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-12-05)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nccs.nasa.gov/news-events/nccs-highlights/nasa-deepened-our-understanding-of-earth-in-2023">Go to NCCS Feature</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/image-article/nasa-september-2023-temperature-data-shows-continued-record-warming/">September 2023 Temperature Data Shows Continued Record Warming</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/image-article/nasa-september-2023-temperature-data-shows-continued-record-warming/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202310_news_gistemp_1472x960.gif" style="border:0" alt="Line plots of the monthly global temperature anomaly showing that recent months have experienced record warmth, with September 1983 the largest anomaly yet recorded." /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>Continuing the temperature trend from this summer, September 2023 was the hottest September on record, according to scientists at NASA’s Goddard Institute for Space Studies.<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-10-13)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/image-article/nasa-september-2023-temperature-data-shows-continued-record-warming/">Go to NASA Release</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/151929/indonesian-fires-return-in-2023">Indonesian Fires Return in 2023</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/151929/indonesian-fires-return-in-2023"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202310_feature_smoke_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Satellite image of smoke rising from fires on Borneo" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>After several years of comparatively quiet fire seasons, Indonesia saw the return of intense, smoky fires in 2023. The blazes have been exacerbated by dry conditions made worse by the return of El Ni&ntilde;o.<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-10-07)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/151929/indonesian-fires-return-in-2023">Go to NASA EO Feature</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-announces-summer-2023-hottest-on-record">NASA Announces Summer 2023 Hottest on Record</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-announces-summer-2023-hottest-on-record"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202309_news_gistemp_736x480.jpg" style="border:0" alt="This map shows monthly temperature anomalies measure from 1880 to August 2023 measured with respect to a the baseline period 1951-1980." /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>Summer of 2023 was Earth's hottest since global records began in 1880, according to scientists at NASA's Goddard Institute of Space Studies.<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-09-14)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-announces-summer-2023-hottest-on-record">Go to NASA Release</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/151743/the-ocean-has-a-fever">The Ocean Has a Fever</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/151743/the-ocean-has-a-fever"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202308_feature_oceanfever_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Partial global map showing sea surface temperature anomalies on Aug 21, 2023" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>Decades of gradual warming due to human-caused climate change and an El Ni&ntilde;o in the Pacific Ocean nudged global sea surface temperatures to record levels in 2023.<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-08-25)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/151743/the-ocean-has-a-fever">Go to NASA EO Feature</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/151699/july-2023-was-the-hottest-month-on-record">July 2023 Was the Hottest Month on Record</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/151699/july-2023-was-the-hottest-month-on-record"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202308_feature_julytemps_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Partial global map showing July 2023 temperature anomalies" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>
July 2023 was hotter than any other month in the global temperature record, according to an analysis by scientists at NASA’s Goddard Institute for Space Studies.
<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-08-15)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/151699/july-2023-was-the-hottest-month-on-record">Go to NASA EO Feature</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->






